[C] State whether the following statements are True or False.

1. The value of an automatic storage class persists between various
   function invocations - False

2. If the CPU registers are not avaliable,the register storage class
   variables are treated as static storage class variables - False

3. The register storage class variables cannot hold float values- True

4. If we try to use register storage class for a float variable the
   compiler will report an error message - False

5. The default value for automatic variable is zero- False

6. The life of static variable is till the control remains within the
   block in which it is defined- False

7. If a global variable is to be defined ,then the extern keyword is
   necessary in its declaration - False

8. The address of register variable is not accessible - False 



